cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.HC. 

The paper proposes a machine learning framework for classifying subjects with Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD) from healthy subjects using fMRI data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) as fMRI data is a type of medical imaging. The paper also mentions the use of an autoencoder and a single layer perceptron, indicating the relevance of sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact on the diagnostic process, indicating relevance to sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
